						<summary>

						<p>Pāṇḍya, Sundarapāṇḍya, 14th year = c. 13th-14th Century.</p>						

						<p>This records that the <hi rend="italic">araiyakaḷ</hi> of the ‘five families’ <hi rend="italic">(añjukuḍi)</hi> unanimously decided to gift a half of all the taxes collected on shops and tolls for repairs to the temple at Aḻimbil.</p>						

						<p>[Published in <hi rend="italic">IPS</hi>, No. 522.]</p>						

